            <p>
                Welcome to our exploration of web development fundamentals. The journey to building beautiful and functional websites begins with two core technologies: HTML and CSS.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>HTML</strong> provides the structure of your content, defining elements like headings, paragraphs, and lists. <strong>CSS</strong>, on the other hand, is the language you use to style that content, adding colors, fonts, and layouts.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section id="box-model-section">
            <h2>Understanding the CSS Box Model</h2>
            <div class="box-model-example">
                <h3>The Box Model Explained</h3>
                <p>
                    Every element on a webpage is a rectangular box. The CSS Box Model describes how these boxes are rendered, allowing you to control their size and spacing.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>**Content:** The actual content of the element, such as text or images.</li>
                    <li>**Padding:** The space between the content and the border.</li>
                    <li>**Border:** The line that surrounds the padding and content.</li>
                    <li>**Margin:** The space outside the border, which separates the element from other elements.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

